                <p>In 1999 Cricket World Cup, Ganguly set the record for the highest score by an Indian and the second highest ever in world cup history with a blitzkrieg of 183 runs off just 158 balls which is the highest score by an Indian in world cup. He also entered into a 318-run partnership with Rahul Dravid which proved to be the highest ever in world cup and the second highest ever in ODI cricket history. He was especially prolific through the off side, earning the nickname&nbsp;‘<strong>God of the Off-Side’ from Rahul Dravid</strong>&nbsp;for his elegant strokeplay square of the&nbsp;wicket and through the&nbsp;covers.</p>
                <p>Eventually, the lady luck smiled on him as he was nominated to Captain Indian Cricket team in 2000. History was in the making as Ganguly led India to unchartered territories of success to emerge as one of the most successful captains ever in the international cricketing arena.&nbsp;India made the ICC Knockout tournament finals where Ganguly scored 100s both in Semi-final and Final and till date only man to do so in an ICC event. On November 3rd 2001 he became a proud father of a sweet young girl Sana.</p>
